        <td>4xx → terminal (no retry), 5xx → retryable with backoff, 429 → rate-limited with Retry-After</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td><a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/Navigator/onLine">navigator.onLine</a></td>
        <td>Baseline</td>
        <td>Detects offline state to queue operations; listens for <code>online</code> event to trigger queued retries</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td><a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/Background_Synchronization_API">Background Sync API</a></td>
        <td>Limited (Chrome)</td>
        <td>Progressive enhancement: if SW registered, queued mutations use Background Sync; otherwise falls back to <code>online</code> event</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td><a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/AbortController">AbortController</a></td>
        <td>Baseline</td>
        <td>Each retry attempt gets a fresh signal; previous attempt aborted before retry dispatches</td>
    </tr>
</table>

